Package ru.tinkoff.qa.neptune.core.api.event.firing.annotation

Annotation Type MakeFileCapturesOnFinishing

  • @Retention(RUNTIME)
@Target(TYPE)
public @interface MakeFileCapturesOnFinishing
    This annotation is designed to mark subclasses of MakesCapturesOnFinishing. When a class is marked by this annotation then it means that it is needed to produce a File after invocation of Consumer.accept(Object) or Function.apply(Object) on built resulted Consumer/Function. This file is produced by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object)

    NOTE 1

    This file is produced if there is any subclass of FileCaptor or Captor that may produce a File.

    NOTE 2

    A subclass of FileCaptor or Captor should be able to handle input values of Consumer.accept(Object) and/or resulted values of Function.apply(Object).
